he immediately fell backward .
the stranger placed the point of his sword at his throat ; and monsieur porthos , finding himself at the mercy of his adversary , acknowledged himself conquered .
upon which the stranger asked his name , and learning that it was porthos , and not dartagnan , he assisted him to rise , brought him back to the hotel , mounted his horse , and disappeared . "
" so it was with monsieur dartagnan this stranger meant to quarrel ? "
" it appears so . "
