he followed him . at a solitary and retired part of the road he drew his sword , and required the messenger to deliver up to him the papers of which he was the bearer . the messenger resisted ; my brother killed him . "
" oh ! " said mme . bonacieux , shuddering .
" remember , that was the only means .
then my brother determined to substitute cunning for force . he took the papers , and presented himself here as the emissary of the cardinal , and in an hour or two a carriage will come to take me away by the orders of his eminence . " " i understand .
it is your brother who sends this carriage . " " exactly ; but that is not all .
that letter you have received , and which you believe to be from madame de chevreuse-- "
