chapter xxxiii
i heard a noise : the wind , i thought , shook the door . no ; it was st . john rivers , who , lifting the latch , came in out of the frozen hurricane -- the howling darkness -- and stood before me : the cloak that covered his tall figure all white as a glacier .
i was almost in consternation , so little had i expected any guest from the blocked - up vale that night .
